). In lateral view, epandrium rectangular, longer than high, with two small acute processes, length about half that of epandrium; gonocoxites fused, apically round, gonostyli rod-shaped, acute apically, deeply inserted in gonocoxites, medially with well sclerotized denticles; in lateral view, basal aedeagal apodeme subrectangular, extending forward as long process.
